      • sampling

        public Object[][] sampling(int frequency)
                    throws IOException
        Return a sorted 2-d array (row-columns) of all objects at the given frequency per second. Note: when we round to the nearest frequency time, it would be better to pick a value at the time closer to the frequency time even if we bend the rules a little bit outside the start/end time filtering but nearer to the frequency time.
        Parameters:
        frequency - the objects per second (e.g. 1Hz = 1000 frequency)
        Returns:
        objects
        Throws:
        IOException - if occurs

      • comp

        protected void comp(ArrayList<VDataObjectValueArray> arrs,
                    Instant time,
                    Integer colidx,
                    String[] subNames,
                    Integer[] subIndices,
                    int[] result)
        Compare time to object list's times. The object list is sorted. If there is a matching time, return its position; otherwise return an appropriate position for insert. The compare result will be stored in the passed-in result array. Array's first item is the found index, the second item is whether at the position is a matching time or not.
        Parameters:
        arrs - the list of object arrays
        time - the time to compare
        result - the compare results
